# Screenshots: placeholder replaced

Yeh file pehle ek invalid placeholder thi jisse images GitHub pe show nahi ho rahi thi. Maine isse ab instructions aur examples wali file mein badal diya hai taaki aap (ya main agar aap images bhejein) screenshots ko sahi tarike se add kar saken.

Kya karna hai (2 options):

1) Agar aap khud images upload karna chahte ho (GitHub web se, sabse aasan):
   - Repo page → Add file → Upload files → drag & drop apne PNG/JPG files ko into a folder named `screenshots/` → Commit changes.
   - Fir apne README.md mein ya jis bhi Markdown file mein dikhana hai, yeh markup use karo:

     ```markdown
     ![Alt text](./screenshots/shot1.png)
     ![Alt text](./screenshots/shot2.png)
     ```

   - Agar direct raw URL use karna ho (branch name ko replace karo):

     ```markdown
     ![Alt text](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rajpootpriyanshi23-AI/ThermoFlip/<branch>/screenshots/shot1.png)
     ```

2) Agar aap chahte ho main karoon:
   - Aap images (PNG/JPG) yahan attach kar do ya mujhe unke public URLs de do.
   - Main phir in files ko repo ke `screenshots/` folder mein add kar dunga aur README.md ko update karke image embed bhi kar dunga.

Git (local) se karne ke liye commands (agar aap terminal use karte ho):

```bash
# create folder and copy images into it
mkdir -p screenshots
cp /path/to/your/shot1.png screenshots/
cp /path/to/your/shot2.png screenshots/

# stage and commit
git add screenshots/shot1.png screenshots/shot2.png
git commit -m "Add real screenshots"
git push
```

Quick checklist agar images show nahin ho rahi ho:
- Files actual image hain (PNG/JPG), text file nahi.
- Path aur filename case-sensitive sahi ho.
- README ya markdown file mein jo path likha hai woh correct relative path ho.
- Agar raw.githubusercontent URL use kar rahe ho to branch name sahi ho.

Aap kya karna chahte ho? A) Main abhi koi changes aur push karun to aap mujhe images attach kar do, ya B) main sirf README/guide update karke rakh doon (maine yeh file updates kar di hai).